<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBC-ASU-NOTEBOOK-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
BACKUP QB JOB ELLIOTT'S, IT APPEARS 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By PAOLA BOIVIN  
 c.1998 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   PROVO, Utah _  &UR; Chad Elliott appears to have won the backup
quarterback job for Arizona State.
</P>
<P>
   The sophomore replaced  &UR; Ryan Kealy late in the fourth quarter
against Brigham Young on Saturday night. He was 4 of 7 for 45
yards. Starter Kealy was 16 of 34 for 241 yards, one touchdown and
one interception.
</P>
<P>
   Elliott was battling senior  &UR; Steve Campbell for the role. ASU
Coach
 &UR; Bruce Snyder said after Camp Tontozona that the competition was
even. They are both listed on the depth chart as No. 2. &QL; 
Versatile J.R. &QL; 
 &UR; J.R. Redmond made his first appearance on defense of the season
with 10:30 remaining in the first quarter.
</P>
<P>
   His appearances on that side of the ball were limited the rest
of the game. The Sun Devils needed him more as a tailback and punt
returner, although he didn't have much success in either area.
</P>
<P>
   ``Personally, I felt I played OK,'' Redmond said. ``I can't
speak for the rest of the team.
</P>
<P>
   ``We really can't talk much about this game until we look at
film and figure out what happened.''
</P>
<P>
   Redmond's three punt returns resulted in just eight yards.
</P>
<P>
   ``They have one of the great threats in J.R. Redmond, and I
thought we did a great job to stop them,'' BYU Coach  &UR; LaVell
Edwards said. &QL; 
Tough break &QL; 
ASU guard  &UR; Randy Leaphart injured his right knee in the first
quarter and didn't play the remainder of the game.
</P>
<P>
   He will undergo further tests today. &QL; 
Will, but no way &QL; 
 &UR; Will Snowden, the Cougars' leading rusher in their opener against
Alabama, was kept out of the game with a pulled hamstring. &QL; 
Injured Cougar &QL; 
BYU starting linebacker  &UR; Brad Martin was involved in a traffic
accident Friday afternoon while drive to practice at Cougar
Stadium.
</P>
<P>
   He received a cut on his forehead that required seven stitches
by the team orthopedist. He played Saturday and was a factor in
stopping ASU's running game. &QL; 
Levi blues &QL; 
What is it about ASU players and elevators?
</P>
<P>
   Defensive end  &UR; Levi Jones spend 20 minutes trapped in a hotel
elevator Friday. He rang the bell until hotel personnel helped him.
</P>
<P>
   During NCAA Tournament play last season, several ASU baseball
players were trapped in a hotel elevator for half an hour before a
game. &QL; 
Quick hits &QL; 
Three true freshmen made the trip: tight end  &UR; Todd Heap,
linebacker &UR; Alfred Williams and defensive back  &UR; William Daniel.
</P>
<P>
   The Sun Devils are now 6-2 in games following a loss in the same
season.
</P>
<P>
   Utah encountered some of its strangest weather in years
Saturday. A tornado, rare in these parts, was spotted north of Salt
Lake. Hail hit Provo and blanketed Cougar Stadium several hours
before the game. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   The Sun Devils have won 10 of their past 12 road games.
</P>
<P>
   Talk about pressure. During an appearance on CNN's ``Larry
King'' ``Live'' this week, LDS Church President  &UR; Gordon B. Hinckley
said he'd like to see BYU's football team have a better season than
last year's 6-5 record. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
