   FINANCIAL
</P>
<P>
   (Coded f)
</P>
<P>
   ASIA-RECESSION (Tokyo) _ As statistics and despair pile up in
Asian countries, it is becoming clear that Asia's recession is
deepening, along with the economic devastation it brings. By Sheryl
WuDunn.
</P>
<P>
   ARGENTINA-ECON (Buenos Aires) _ It has become almost a daily
ritual. President Carlos Saul Menem and his chief economic advisers
take every opportunity to promise they will not retreat from the
government's fixed exchange rate that pegs the value of the
Argentine peso to the American dollar one to one. Such
pronouncements have often preceded huge devaluations in Latin
America. But most Argentine economists and Wall Street analysts are
taking Menem at his word, at least for now, despite concerns that
the currency peg could push up interest rates and unemployment. By
Clifford Krauss.
</P>
<P>
   PAPER-MAKER (Cicinnati) _ There was a time when it was thought
that computers and computer networking would usher in the era of
the ``paperless office.'' Not only has that fallacy been shot down,
but one of the biggest paper makers, International Paper, has
proven to be a particularly zealous adopter of information
technology. Here's a look at how a company in an old-line
manufacturing industry has incorporated computer networking into
every fiber of its business.
</P>
<P>
   NOVELL-MAJOR-PROFILE (Undated) _ Profile of Drew Major, the
software designer who is leading Novell's apparent comeback. By
John Markoff.
</P>
<P>
   FRONTIER-PROSPECTS (Undated) _ A look at the Frontier Corp. and
its merger prospects as its chief executive consolidates his
strategic plan and the stock price heads south. By Seth Schiesel.
</P>
<P>
   MICROSOFT-SUIT-ASSESS (Washington) _ Analysis: what to make of
the Microsoft case now, in light of Friday's hearing. By Joel
Brinkley.
</P>
<P>
   FBI-FCC-SURVEILLANCE (Undated) _ In a setback for the FBI, the
Federal Communications Commission has given the telecommunications
industry an additional 20 months to comply with a federal law meant
to bring law enforcement surveillance into the digital age. By John
Markoff.
</P>
<P>
   DIGICOM-COLUMN (Undated) _ The Digital Commerce column; details
TK. By Denise Caruso.
</P>
<P>
   SEMICONDUCTOR-MARKETPLACE (Undated) _ Are things looking up for
the semiconductor market?
</P>
<P>
   ECON-CALENDAR (Undated) _ Key government figures this week.
</P>
