<P>
   NIRELAND-CHANGE (Dundalk, Ireland) _ Optimism is a sudden
newcomer to the North, but it's getting a warm welcome. People are
daring to put their frequently battered faith in a political
solution to the tribal conflict that has cost more than 3,200
lives, and there are convincing signs of cooperation in Belfast
between leaders of the warring Catholic and Protestant communities
who have battled and shunned one another for generations. By Warren
Hoge.
</P>
<P>
   INDIAN-RESERVATIONS-TOURISM (Umatilla Reservation, Ore.) _
American Indian reservations, long considered economic deserts
amidst a landscape of general prosperity, are finding that they
have a lot more to offer the world than casinos and art galleries _
they have their homes, their backyards, their stories. Visitors,
especially a growing number of Europeans, are traveling to some of
the country's most remote places in search of a life many Americans
overlook on their vacations.
</P>
<P>
   BBO-SOSA-HOMERUN (Chicago) _ Sammy Sosa knows he's only a
footnote in history at the moment; but with 62 home runs, and with
Mark McGwire having cooled off, he could yet end up being the
single-season home run king.
</P>
<P>
   TEN-USOPEN-MEN (New York) _ U.S. Open men's final. By Robin
Finn.
</P>
