<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Roseanne short on words about talk show
 &HT;    By Drew Jubera
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ ``Daytime is where things are being said,'' said
Roseanne, before she said very little about her talk show, which
debuts today at 5 p.m. on WGNX.
</P>
<P>
   Could she tell us something about the first show?
</P>
<P>
   ``No.''
</P>
<P>
   Just a little?
</P>
<P>
   ``No.''
</P>
<P>
   A teeny . . .
</P>
<P>
   ``You just have to watch it. I'm not going to hype it,'' she
said during a conference call designed to hype the show to
reporters around the country.
</P>
<P>
   ``If I hype it, two things happen,'' Roseanne went on. ``As soon
as you say what you're doing, it's stolen immediately. And you
can't talk about this stuff. You have to see it. It'll ruin the
surprise.''
</P>
<P>
   What's been stolen so far, considering that, you know, the show
hasn't aired yet?
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm not going to answer any of that.''
</P>
<P>
   A call was placed to King World, the show's syndicator, to shed
a different light on things.
</P>
<P>
   Do you know who's going to be on the first show?
</P>
<P>
   ``No,'' said publicist Randi Cone.
</P>
<P>
   No.
</P>
<P>
   ``They're trying to be flexible. They're taping Whoopi Goldberg
today (Friday). But they're going to pick the best show for the
first one.''
</P>
<P>
   Roseanne, former sitcom star and ``Star Spangled Banner''
stylist, has already taped about 10 shows. Among the guests who'll
appear the next couple of weeks: Dennis Rodman, Ellen DeGeneres,
Judge Judy, Dame Edna, Reba McEntire, Tori Amos, Patti LaBelle.
</P>
<P>
   Did Roseanne tape each show as if it were the premiere, with
references to it being her first show?
</P>
<P>
   Pause.
</P>
<P>
   ``Needless to say,'' said Cone, ``as the PR person for the
company, I didn't choose to do it this way.''
</P>
<P>
   Pause.
</P>
<P>
   ``Watch the show,'' Cone finally said. She sounded really nice.
``She (Roseanne) is so good. There's nothing like it.''
</P>
<P>
   Nothing like it?
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm a fan of everyone who's ever had a talk show,'' Roseanne
said. ``And I'm stealing from all of them.''
</P>
<P>
   There you have it.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
