<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Maddux's injury first felt last week
 &HT;    By Thomas Stinson
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Greg Maddux first felt something in his last start
Tuesday in Montreal, discomfort under his right armpit. Trainers
treated him for a couple days and he thought little more of it.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's kind of hard to get something treated that doesn't
hurt,'' Maddux said. ``I got treatment the first day or so and I
figured maybe it was just sore. Who knows why? Maybe it's the
innings or just getting older.''
</P>
<P>
   That was the best, if only, explanation for the muscle strain
under the right arm that sidelined Maddux Sunday, when the same
pain returned. Though Maddux doubted it would cause him to miss any
time, the news was hardly encouraging to the Braves after a 6-5
loss to Florida.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think it's going to be fine,'' said manager Bobby Cox.
``That's a very unusual place. His elbow is fine. Everything else
is fine. He just came up (after the sixth) and said this was really
tight and it wouldn't loosen up. So I'm absolutely not taking any
chances.''
</P>
<P>
   Maddux will start a sequence of ultra-sound and
eletro-stimulation treatments but did not know when he might try to
throw again. The injury came just as he appeared to regain form,
following two straight losses. Before coming out with a 1-0 lead
Sunday, Maddux had thrown 10 scoreless innings and allowed two hits
with 10 strikeouts.
</P>
<P>
   ``Time is probably better (treatment) than anything,'' he said.
``Just a couple days.''
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
